President Muhammadu Buhari, on Tuesday, joined Bola Tinubu, the All Progressives Congress (APC) flag-bearer, for the grand finale of the party’s presidential campaign. The rally held at the Teslim Balogun stadium in Surulere, Lagos state. Speaking at the campaign, Tinubu said he will “work hard” for the country if elected. Kashim Shettima, the APC vice presidential candidate; Femi Gbajabiamila, speaker of the house of representatives; Abdullahi Adamu, APC national chairperson, Remi Tinubu, wife of the presidential candidate; Babajide Sanwo-Olu, governor of Lagos, and his deputy, Obafemi Hamzat, were among those present at the rally. Buhari also endorsed Sanwo-Olu, who is seeking re-election as governor of Lagos. Below are photos.                   